_header: Sir at this feast of beneficence
_description: William Dunbar, ‘Quhone mony benefices vakit’ — three 5-line stanzas

CULLl510.First Lines:
Schir at þis fast of beneficethink þat small partis makis
                    gvyt seruice…
CULLl510.Last Lines:
…Latt anes þe cop go round abouttAnd win the couanes
                    bennisoune
